 :W2K bug: [from `Y2K bug' for the Year 2000 problem] The deployment of
Microsoft's Windows 2000 operating system, which hackers generally expect
will turn out to have been among the worst train wrecks in the history of
software engineering. Such is the power of Microsoft marketing, however, that
it is also expected this will not become obvious until it has incurred
hundreds of millions of dollars in downtime and lost opportunity costs.